dering robust methods**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether I should make this method robust by using the `@Test` approach that accesses the root loader only if the jar path exists. Would that mean I could implement a skip or early return mechanism? But then again, I shouldn't skip native checks with assume or guard clauses if the necessary properties aren't found. I just need to ensure I'm not violating any conditions.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_QFhelhxUn5w7CFugT7KZan5I|fc_06fcb496b6589a68016a3fbbd3cd3c8195b02dacd2c394007d", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bc_fips/ProvXDHPrivateKeyTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;", "newText": "import java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectStreamClass;"}, {"oldText": "        byte[] baseSerializedKey = serializedAsBasePrivateKey(\n                serialize(providerPrivateKey), providerPrivateKey.getClass().getName());\n\n        PrivateKey basePrivateKey = assertInstanceOf(\n                PrivateKey.class, deserialize(baseSerializedKey));", "newText": "        PrivateKey basePrivateKey = assertInstanceOf(\n                PrivateKey.class,\n                deserializeAsBasePrivateKey(\n                        serialize(providerPrivateKey), providerPrivateKey.getClass().getName()));"}, {"oldText": "    private static byte[] serializedAsBasePrivateKey(\n            byte[] providerSerializedKey, String providerClassName) {\n        if (PROVIDER_PRIVATE_KEY_CLASS_NAME.equals(providerClassName)) {\n            return providerSerializedKey;\n        }\n\n        assertEquals(PROVIDER_JDK11_PRIVATE_KEY_CLASS_NAME, providerClassName);\n        return replaceSerializedClassName(\n                providerSerializedKey,\n                PROVIDER_JDK11_PRIVATE_KEY_CLASS_NAME,\n                PROVIDER_PRIVATE_KEY_CLASS_NAME);\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] replaceSerializedClassName(\n            byte[] serializedValue, String sourceClassName, String targetClassName) {\n        byte[] sourceName = sourceClassName.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n        byte[] targetName = targetClassName.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n        int sourceNameOffset = findUniqueOffset(serializedValue, sourceName);\n        int lengthOffset = sourceNameOffset - 2;\n\n        assertEquals(sourceName.length, readUnsignedShort(serializedValue, lengthOffset));\n\n        ByteArrayOutputStream output = new ByteArrayOutputStream(\n                serializedValue.length - sourceName.length + targetName.length);\n        output.write(serializedValue, 0, lengthOffset);\n        output.write((targetName.length >>> 8) & 0xff);\n        output.write(targetName.length & 0xff);\n        output.write(targetName, 0, targetName.length);\n        output.write(\n                serializedValue,\n                sourceNameOffset + sourceName.length,\n                serializedValue.length - sourceNameOffset - sourceName.length);\n        return output.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static int findUniqueOffset(byte[] value, byte[] target) {\n        int result = -1;\n        int matches = 0;\n        for (int i = 0; i <= value.length - target.length; i++) {\n            if (matchesAt(value, target, i)) {\n                result = i;\n                matches++;\n            }\n        }\n        assertEquals(1, matches);\n        return result;\n    }\n\n    private static boolean matchesAt(byte[] value, byte[] target, int offset) {\n        for (int i = 0; i < target.length; i++) {\n            if (value[offset + i] != target[i]) {\n                return false;\n            }\n        }\n        return true;\n    }\n\n    private static int readUnsignedShort(byte[] value, int offset) {\n        return ((value[offset] & 0xff) << 8) | (value[offset + 1] & 0xff);\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static Object deserializeAsBasePrivateKey(\n            byte[] serializedValue, String providerClassName) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayInputStream input = new ByteArrayInputStream(serializedValue);\n        try (ObjectInputStream objectInput =\n                new BasePrivateKeyObjectInputStream(input, providerClassName)) {\n            return objectInput.readObject();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class BasePrivateKeyObjectInputStream extends ObjectInputStream {\n        private final String providerClassName;\n\n        BasePrivateKeyObjectInputStream(\n                ByteArrayInputStream input, String providerClassName) throws Exception {\n            super(input);\n            this.providerClassName = providerClassName;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> resolveClass(ObjectStreamClass descriptor)\n                throws IOException, ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (PROVIDER_PRIVATE_KEY_CLASS_NAME.equals(providerClassName)) {\n                return super.resolveClass(descriptor);\n            }\n            assertEquals(PROVIDER_JDK11_PRIVATE_KEY_CLASS_NAME, providerClassName);\n            if (PROVIDER_JDK11_PRIVATE_KEY_CLASS_NAME.equals(descriptor.getName())) {\n                return Class.forName(PROVIDER_PRIVATE_KEY_CLASS_NAME);\n            }\n            return super.resolveClass(descriptor);\n        }\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1386, "output": 2237, "cacheRead": 50688, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 54311, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782561728249, "responseId": "resp_06fcb496b6589a68016a3fbbc0edc081958a8a9d60bd6cabf6"}}
